---
title: "HOME"
layout: "base.ejs"
---

<!--11ty works in a specific way, using something called
'front matter'. Basically, 11ty sends through this front matter
(the above metadata), and drops it into our ejs template in _includes 'base.ejs'
layout is a special tag from 11ty, but title is simply sent through as ejs variable!-->

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container flow">
      <div class="hero__content flow">
        <h1 class="section-title">Welcome to my blog!</h1>
        <p>I use this space to document my adventures in front-end development, sharing how I’ve overcome issues I’ve
          run into, useful resources, and more.</p>
        <p>Below are some of my favourite articles, or you can go to the blog page to see my most recent posts.</p>
        <div class="flex-group">
          <a href="#featured-articles" class="btn btn--primary">Featured articles</a>
          <a href="/blog/" class="btn btn--neutral">Most recent articles</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <img src="//unsplash.it/510" alt="" class="hero__image">
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="featured-articles" class="featured-articles">
    <div class="container flow">
      <h2 class="section-title text-center ">Featured articles</h2>
      <p class="text-center">Here is a sample of articles which I feel give you a good idea of what this site is all
        about.</p>
      <ul role="list" class="articles__list flow">
        <% for(let post of collections.featured){ %> 
        <%- include('_includes/article-snippet.ejs', { post }); -%>
        <% } %> 
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>